# LGLC Website Templates - Cursor Rules

This project uses a token-based design system for the Lesbian and Gay Liberation in Canada (LGLC) website templates.

## Core Principles

1. **Always use design tokens** - Never hardcode CSS values. All styling must use tokens from `css/design-tokens.css`
2. **Mobile-first responsive design** - Design for mobile first, enhance for larger screens
3. **Accessibility first** - Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible and meet WCAG 2.1 standards
4. **Semantic HTML** - Use proper HTML5 elements and ARIA attributes
5. **Component isolation** - Each component in its own CSS file

## CSS Rules

### Design Token Usage

**✅ DO:**
- Always use design tokens via `var(--token-name)`
- Reference tokens from `css/design-tokens.css`
- Use semantic token names when available (`--text-primary` over `--color-primary-black`)

**❌ DON'T:**
- Never hardcode values (no `16px`, `#ED1C24`, `8px`, etc.)
- Never use raw `px` values for spacing, fonts, or sizes (except border widths which are already in tokens)
- Never define custom values in component CSS files

### CSS File Structure

1. **Import order is critical:**
   ```html
   <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/design-tokens.css">
   <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/your-component.css">
   ```

2. **Component files:**
   - Each component gets its own CSS file in `css/` directory
   - Import `design-tokens.css` first in HTML
   - Use design tokens exclusively

3. **Units:**
   - Use `rem` for all scalable values (spacing, fonts, sizes) via tokens
   - Use `px` ONLY for border widths (already defined in tokens)
   - Never mix units

### Example CSS:
```css
/* ✅ Correct */
.my-component {
  padding: var(--spacing-4);
  color: var(--color-primary-red);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
}

/* ❌ Incorrect */
.my-component {
  padding: 16px;
  color: #ED1C24;
  border-radius: 8px;
  font-size: 18px;
}
```

## HTML Rules

### Semantic HTML
- Use semantic HTML5 elements: `<header>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<section>`
- Include ARIA labels where needed
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)

### Structure
- No inline styles - keep all CSS in stylesheets
- Import CSS in correct order (design-tokens.css first)
- Include `js/header.js` before closing `</body>` tag

## JavaScript Rules

### File Organization
- Component-specific JS in `js/` directory
- Keep JavaScript vanilla (no frameworks)
- Ensure accessibility features (keyboard navigation, ARIA updates)

### Accessibility
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Include focus management
- Provide screen reader announcements where needed

## Component Creation Guidelines

### When creating a new component:

1. **Create CSS file:**
   - New file in `css/` directory
   - Name it descriptively (e.g., `card.css`, `button.css`)

2. **Use design tokens:**
   - Reference existing tokens via `var(--token-name)`
   - If you need a new value, add it to `css/design-tokens.css` first
   - Never define custom values in component CSS

3. **Follow existing patterns:**
   - Look at `css/header.css` and `css/footer.css` for examples
   - Maintain consistency with existing components

## Design Token Categories

### Colors
- Primary: `--color-primary-red`, `--color-primary-navy`, `--color-primary-yellow`, `--color-primary-black`, `--color-primary-gray`
- Secondary: `--color-secondary-*` variants
- Semantic: `--text-primary`, `--text-secondary`, `--text-tertiary`, `--text-inverse`
- Backgrounds: `--bg-page`, `--bg-surface`, `--bg-elevated`

### Spacing
- Use `--spacing-1` through `--spacing-24` (0.25rem to 6rem)
- Never hardcode spacing values

### Typography
- Font sizes: `--font-size-xs` through `--font-size-5xl`
- Font weights: `--font-weight-normal` through `--font-weight-extrabold`
- Line heights: `--line-height-tight`, `--line-height-normal`, `--line-height-relaxed`, `--line-height-loose`

### Borders
- Widths: `--border-width-thin`, `--border-width-medium`, `--border-width-thick`
- Radius: `--border-radius-sm` through `--border-radius-2xl`
- Colors: `--border-color-*`

### Shadows
- `--shadow-xs` through `--shadow-2xl`

## Responsive Design

### Breakpoints
- Mobile-first approach (default styles for mobile)
- Tablet: `48rem` (768px) - use `@media (min-width: 48rem)`
- Desktop: `64rem` (1024px) - use `@media (min-width: 64rem)`
- Large Desktop: `80rem` (1280px) - use `@media (min-width: 80rem)`

**Note:** CSS variables cannot be used in `@media` queries, so use the values directly with comments:
```css
@media (min-width: 48rem) {  /* --breakpoint-md */
  /* Tablet styles */
}
```

## Accessibility Requirements

### Focus States
- Always include: Yellow outline (`--color-primary-yellow`)
- Adequate offset (`--outline-offset-sm`)
- Visible on all interactive elements

### Touch Targets
- Minimum size: `var(--touch-target-min)` (2.75rem/44px)
- Ensure buttons and links have sufficient clickable area

### Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Logical tab order
- Skip links for main content
- ARIA labels where needed

## Button Guidelines

### Primary Button (`.btn-primary`)
- Use for: Main call-to-action, primary user actions
- Black background (`--color-primary-black`), white text
- Focus: Yellow outline

### Secondary Button (`.btn-secondary`)
- Use for: Secondary actions, alternative options
- Transparent background, black text, gray border
- Focus: Yellow outline

## Card Guidelines

### Content Cards (`.card`)
- White background
- Use for: Content previews, feature highlights, grid layouts
- Hover: Slight lift, enhanced shadow
- Focus: Yellow outline

### Related Results Cards (`.related-card`)
- Use for: Related content on detail pages
- Icon/image at top, heading, list of items
- 3-column grid on desktop

## Typography Guidelines

### Font Sizes
- **5xl (3rem)**: Hero titles, landing page main headings
- **4xl (2.25rem)**: Section titles, major page headings
- **3xl (1.875rem)**: Subsection headings, large content titles
- **2xl (1.5rem)**: Medium headings, section subheadings
- **xl (1.25rem)**: Small headings, card titles
- **lg (1.125rem)**: Large body text, emphasized content
- **base (1rem)**: Default body text, buttons, form inputs
- **sm (0.875rem)**: Small text, captions, metadata
- **xs (0.75rem)**: Tiny text, fine print

### Font Weights
- **Extrabold (800)**: Hero titles, major emphasis
- **Bold (700)**: Section headings, important content
- **Semibold (600)**: Buttons, card titles, emphasized text
- **Medium (500)**: Navigation links, subheadings
- **Normal (400)**: Body text, default weight

## Layout Patterns

### Containers
- `.landing-container`: Landing page sections (max-width: 75rem)
- `.record-container`: Individual record pages (max-width: 80rem)
- `.search-section`: Search page content (max-width: 72.5rem)

### Grids
- `.cards-grid`: 3-column grid, stacks to 1 column on mobile
- Gap: `--spacing-8`

